              "type": "output_text",
              "text": "To solve **17 * 19**, we can use the property of differences of squares or a simple distributive method.\n\n### Reasoning:\nOne of the easiest ways to calculate this mentally is to treat 19 as (20 - 1).\n\n1.  **Distributive Property:**\n    Multiply 17 by 20 and then subtract 17 multiplied by 1:\n    $17 \\times 19 = 17 \\times (20 - 1)$\n    $17 \\times 19 = (17 \\times 20) - (17 \\times 1)$\n\n2.  **Calculate each part:**\n    $17 \\times 20 = 340$\n    $17 \\times 1 = 17$\n\n3.  **Subtract the results:**\n    $340 - 17 = 323$\n\nAlternatively, using the \"average\" method:\nSince 17 and 19 are both 1 unit away from 18, you can use the identity $(x - 1)(x + 1) = x^2 - 1$.\nHere, $x = 18$.\n$18^2 = 324$\n$324 - 1 = 323$\n\nFinal Answer:\n323",
